defaultHeritage and Growthdefault&#xa0;
default9
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultConservation of all heritage assets relies, albeit to differing degrees, on ongoing maintenance and therefore ongoing investment. Economic vitality is therefore 
defaultkey
default to the overall success of conservation in England. 
default&#xa0;
default10
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOur heritage is a major contributor to economic vitality. It provides income to the country through tourism and is frequently the seed-corn of successful, characterful and sustainable regeneration of run-down areas. 
default&#xa0;
default11
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe vast majority of heritage assets are in private hands. The conservation of such assets depends on the motivation of the owners, which in large part will be dictated by their own economics. It is therefore vital that all those involved in conservation understand the position of owners, including businesses, and work with them to find constructive ways of conserving heritage assets – ways that sustain the important heritage value of the asset, whilst providing it with a viable use for the medium to long term.
default&#xa0;default‘Sustainable Development’, Conservation and Growthdefault&#xa0;
default12
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe National Planning Policy Framework (the NPPF) provides a definition of ‘sustainable development’ and policies for planning decisions that encapsulates the tie-in between economic vitality and heritage conservation. It thoughtfully sets out the way in which those twin objectives should be sought in 
defaulta 
defaultway that maximises the potential for both, whilst minimising conflict.
default&#xa0;
default13
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe NPPF effectively governs a great deal of the work that English Heritage is involved in. Where it does not directly apply as a matter of law, English Heritage still sees its principles as applying as a matter of consistent common sense.
default&#xa0;
default14
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultApplying the principles of the NPPF to the work of conservation requires all decision-makers involved in the planning system to be mindful of the objective of heritage regulation and of growth.
default&#xa0;
