defaultEnglish Heritage as a Regulatordefault&#xa0;default20
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnglish Heritage’s role in the protection of the historic environment is frequently misunderstood. English Heritage is principally an expert adviser. It is not a decision-maker in the planning system. Its regulatory activities are very limited:
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default21
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe currently publish around 15 pieces of general advice and guidance annually and are asked to respond to around 22,000 cases from around the country. From this arises an average of around 50 complaints yearly, of which an average of around 5 turn into a threat of judicial review or JR proceedings. 
default&#xa0;
default22
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnglish Heritage is 
defaulttherefore 
defaultvery active in providing advice and guidance to local planning authorities as to the best means of achieving the objectives of the NPPF at the strategic level of making local development plans and on a case-by-case basis. Local planning authorities are bound to take into account such advice in so far as it is in keeping with the NPPF and their existing local development plans. 
default&#xa0;
default23
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs the NPPF and local plans are all directed to the objective of sustainable development, which already has the objectives of growth and heritage conservation (amongst others) written into it, English Heritage’s advice 
defaulthas to be
default mindful of both the conservation and growth impacts. 
default&#xa0;
default24
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnglish Heritage is not responsible for any system of compliance. The impact of its regulatory activities is very limited indeed and in the last year has been negligible.
