defaultmay
default be perceived. As drafted it should not impede the primary statutory objectives of English Heritage’s work. However, if the wording 
defaultwas 
defaultchanged or
default if
default the supporting guidance altered the interpretation and the result was 
defaultan unresolved potential conflict between the primary regulatory objectives and the growth duty, then there could be considerable implications for the work of English Heritage and challenges to it. 
